  <prompt>
    **CONDITIONAL TASK** — only runs if Phase 1 RB-T028 root-cause analysis (task 011 outcome) warrants a NEW binding rule. Decision input: did the cluster fix root-cause point to a generalizable rule about service-registration / endpoint-mapping alignment?

    If YES (Phase 1 task 011 found a binding-rule-worthy pattern): extend `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` § F (added by r1) with a NEW bullet/section codifying the rule. Suggested rule text per FR-08 + spec.md: **"When an endpoint maps unconditionally (registered without feature-flag check), every service the endpoint depends on MUST also be registered unconditionally. Conditional registration of a transitively-required service while the endpoint is unconditional produces metadata-abort errors at request time."**

    If NO (Phase 1 didn't surface a new generalizable rule; the cluster fix was case-specific): document the "no extension warranted" decision in `decisions/D-08-bff-extensions-no-extension.md` and skip the constraint edit.

    🚨 CRITICAL — task-execute MUST refuse Agent delegation for this task. Main session edits `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` directly via the Edit tool. Per CLAUDE.md §3, sub-agents launched via Agent tool CANNOT write to `.claude/` paths; attempting delegation will fail with "Edit denied on `.claude/...`". This is the boundary working correctly. The main session is the ONLY agent permitted to perform this edit. The pattern is established by r1 task 080.

    Per CLAUDE.md §10 (BFF Hygiene), `bff-extensions.md` is the binding pre-merge checklist; any change here affects every BFF-touching task afterward. Precision required.
  </prompt>

  <role>Main-session AI agent extending the BFF-extensions constraint document with a new binding rule (or recording why no rule is warranted).</role>

  <goal>
    Conditional outcome based on Phase 1 task 011 findings:

    **If extension warranted**:
    - `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` § F gains a NEW bullet/sub-section codifying the unconditional-service-registration rule
    - Cross-reference to RB-T028-03/04/05/06 cluster + ADR-010 (DI minimalism) + ADR-018 (kill switches)
    - Existing § F + all prior sections PRESERVED unchanged (additive edit only)
    - Decision record `decisions/D-08-bff-extensions-extension-applied.md` documenting WHY

    **If extension NOT warranted**:
    - `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` UNCHANGED
    - Decision record `decisions/D-08-bff-extensions-no-extension.md` documenting WHY (case-specific cluster fix; no generalizable rule)
    - Cross-reference to RB-T028 cluster resolution

    Either path satisfies FR-08 (per spec.md: "either extension exists OR decision record explains why not").
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="target-constraint-file">.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
    <file purpose="phase-1-cluster-fix-outcome">projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/tasks/011-fix-rb-t028-cluster.poml (read Status/completion notes)</file>
    <file purpose="phase-1-decision-record">projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/decisions/ (look for D-07 + earlier T028-related decisions)</file>
    <file purpose="r1-bff-extensions-task">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/tasks/080-update-bff-extensions-constraint.poml (pattern reference for main-session-only `.claude/` edit)</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="root-claude">CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="spec">projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="design">projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/design.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="FR-08">`.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` § F extended IF Phase 5 finds the unconditional-service-registration rule warranted; otherwise decision record explains why not</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §3">Sub-agent write boundary: sub-agents CANNOT write to `.claude/` paths. Main session ONLY for this edit.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §10">BFF Hygiene — `bff-extensions.md` is the binding pre-merge checklist; any change here affects every BFF-touching task afterward</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">DI minimalism — new rule (if added) MUST be consistent with ADR-010's minimal-DI principle</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-018">Kill switches — new rule (if added) MUST be consistent with ADR-018's feature-flag handling</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-01">No production code changes (`.claude/constraints/` is binding governance doc, not `src/`)</constraint>
    <constraint source="D-04">Phase 4 outputs are pilot-grade; Phase 5 governance updates capture findings, NOT full remediation</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
      <file>CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-010-di-minimalism.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-018-feature-flags.md</file>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/tasks/080-update-bff-extensions-constraint.poml</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per design.md §5.5 + FR-08, this task is CONDITIONAL on Phase 1's root-cause finding. The RB-T028-03/04/05/06 cluster shared one root cause: services registered conditionally (behind feature flags), but the endpoints that depended on them mapped unconditionally. Result: at request time, the endpoint metadata builder aborts because the service can't be resolved.

      The question for r2 Phase 5 is: does this root cause generalize to a binding pre-merge check? If YES, codify in `bff-extensions.md` § F so every future BFF-touching task is required to verify alignment. If NO (the cluster was an isolated case where 4 services shared one feature flag), document the decision and don't add rule weight.

      Per CLAUDE.md §3, sub-agents CANNOT write to `.claude/` paths. This task is the second of r1+r2's main-session-only pattern (r1 task 080 established the pattern for the original § F addition; this task extends it).

      The decision record path (D-08) captures EITHER outcome: extension applied OR not. This is binding per FR-08: "Acceptance: either extension exists OR decision record explains why not."
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="011" status="not-started">Phase 1 RB-T028 cluster fix — provides root-cause finding</dependency>
      <dependency task="080" status="not-started">Phase 5 task 080 (procedure doc update) — for cross-reference consistency</dependency>
    </dependencies>
  </context>

  <relevant-files>
    <file>.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
    <file>projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/decisions/D-08-bff-extensions-{applied|no-extension}.md</file>
  </relevant-files>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read `projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/tasks/011-fix-rb-t028-cluster.poml` (or task-011's completion-notes) and Phase 1 decision records to determine: did the root-cause analysis surface a generalizable rule?</step>
    <step order="2">Read `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` in full to understand existing § F structure (added by r1 task 080).</step>
    <step order="3">Decision: extension warranted? Apply criterion: (a) does the rule prevent a recurring class of bugs (not just the 4-entry T028 cluster); (b) is the rule clearly testable at PR review time; (c) is the rule consistent with ADR-010 + ADR-018?</step>
    <step order="4a">**If EXTENSION WARRANTED**:
      (i) Draft new sub-section in § F: bullet text + rationale + cross-reference to RB-T028 cluster + ADR-010 / ADR-018 / r1 lessons-learned.
      (ii) Apply edit via main-session Edit tool. Verify existing § F + prior sections preserved.
      (iii) Author `decisions/D-08-bff-extensions-extension-applied.md` documenting WHY + the verbatim new text + cross-references.
    </step>
    <step order="4b">**If NO EXTENSION**:
      (i) Author `decisions/D-08-bff-extensions-no-extension.md` documenting WHY (e.g., cluster was case-specific; rule too narrow to add weight to every PR; existing ADR-010 + ADR-018 sufficient).
      (ii) Cross-reference to RB-T028 cluster resolution; cite r1 task 011's findings.
      (iii) `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` UNCHANGED.
    </step>
    <step order="5">Step 9.5 — Run `code-review` + `adr-check` (FULL rigor for binding constraint addition). Verify rule consistency with ADR-010 + ADR-018; verify no ambiguity in rule text.</step>
    <step order="6">Verify `git status` shows ONLY: `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` (if extended) AND `decisions/D-08-*.md` (either path). NO `src/`, NO test, NO other files.</step>
    <step order="7">Commit message:
      - If extended: "docs(.claude): extend bff-extensions § F with unconditional-service-registration rule (FR-08; RB-T028 root cause)"
      - If not: "docs(decisions): D-08 bff-extensions no extension warranted (FR-08; case-specific cluster)"
    </step>
    <step order="8">Update `current-task.md` with completion notes citing the decision path taken + new constraint text (if applied) + cross-references to r1's § F structure.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Read">task 011 outcome, existing constraint file, ADRs</tool>
    <tool name="Edit">main-session-only — `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` (if extension warranted)</tool>
    <tool name="Write">`decisions/D-08-*.md` (either path)</tool>
    <tool name="Skill">code-review (Step 9.5); adr-check (Step 9.5)</tool>
    <tool name="Bash">`git status` for boundary verification; final commit</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="docs-conditional">.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md (updated IF extension warranted)</output>
    <output type="docs">projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/decisions/D-08-bff-extensions-{applied|no-extension}.md</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Decision record `D-08-bff-extensions-*.md` exists documenting the conditional outcome (applied OR no-extension)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">If extension applied: `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` § F shows new sub-section with unconditional-service-registration rule + cross-references to ADR-010, ADR-018, RB-T028 cluster</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">If extension applied: existing § F + all prior sections preserved unchanged (verified via diff)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`git status` shows ONLY `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` (conditional) + `decisions/D-08-*.md` modified</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Edit (if any) performed by main session, NOT delegated to Agent sub-agent — would fail with "Edit denied" per CLAUDE.md §3</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Step 9.5 gates pass: code-review + adr-check (no HIGH findings); rule consistent with ADR-010 + ADR-018</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <execution>
    🚨 MAIN-SESSION-ONLY. task-execute MUST refuse Agent delegation for this task. Main session executes directly. Pattern reference: `projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/tasks/080-update-bff-extensions-constraint.poml` — same boundary handling.

    FULL rigor: Step 9.5 code-review + adr-check required.
  </execution>
